# C2-B3 (HIGH): without this file, `COPY . .` in Dockerfile pulls
# `target/` (potentially several GB on a developer machine), all
# `node_modules/`, `.git/`, plus untracked dot-directories — slowing
# local builds 10×+ and bleeding developer-local files into the build
# context. CI builds are unaffected (clean checkout) but local builds
# bleed.
target/
**/node_modules/
**/.git
**/.git/**
/dist/
/coverage/
/data/
/tmp/
/.planning/
/.research/
/.claude/
CLAUDE.md
*.log
.env
.env.*
